\par \pard\plain \li115\ri130\sb80\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \f7\fs16 
Comic Chat is a comic-strip version of Internet Chat. You can connect to a chat room on an Internet server and conduct real-time conversations with other people. You can pick a cartoon character to represent you, and your conversation appears as word ball
oons in frames of a comic strip. With Comic Chat, you can express a wide range of emotions, send "thoughts," and save the chat session for offline viewing.
\par The Comic Chat window is composed of the following parts:
\par \pard\plain \s27\fi-187\li302\ri130\sb80\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar\tx302 \f7\fs16 \{bmc bullet.bmp\}\tab A "Starring" pane, which prints the title of the chat and lists the participants
\par \pard\plain \s31\fi-187\li302\ri130\sb48\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar\tx302 \f7\fs16 \{bmc bullet.bmp\}\tab The member list pane
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\}\tab The viewing pane, where conversation occurs and chat history appears as a comic strip
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\}\tab A self-view pane, which shows what your character looks like
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\}\tab The emotion wheel
\par \{bmc bullet.bmp\}\tab A compose pane, where you type your messages{\f1 
