\par \pard\plain \s27\fi-187\li302\ri130\sb80\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar\tx302 \f7\fs16 1\tab On the File menu, click New.
\par \pard\plain \s31\fi-187\li302\ri130\sb48\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar\tx302 \f7\fs16 2\tab Click Expand, and then type the name of the server you want to connect to\emdash for example, comicsrv1.microsoft.com.
\par 3\tab Type your TCP/IP port number for the {\ul IRC}{\v GLOSS_IRC} connection. The default number is 6667.
\par 4\tab Type the name of a chat room on a server, beginning with a number symbol (#). If you type a name that does not exist, a new one is created with that name.
\par 5\tab Type your full name.
