\par \pard\plain \li115\ri130\sb80\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \f7\fs16 The following options are available to you in the Connect dialog box.
\par \pard\plain \s2\li115\ri130\sb120\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \b\f7\fs16 Favorites
\par \pard\plain \li115\ri130\sb80\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \f7\fs16 Displays your favorite chat rooms. In the list, select the room you want to enter.
\par \pard\plain \s2\li115\ri130\sb120\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \b\f7\fs16 Server
\par \pard\plain \li115\ri130\sb80\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \f7\fs16 Displays the chat room server. In the box, type the name of the server where the chat room is located.
\par \pard\plain \s2\li115\ri130\sb120\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \b\f7\fs16 Port
\par \pard\plain \li115\ri130\sb80\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \f7\fs16 Displays the port number for the server. In the box, type the name of the port number where the server is located. The default port number is 6667.
\par \pard\plain \s2\li115\ri130\sb120\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \b\f7\fs16 Connect to Specific Channel
\par \pard\plain \li115\ri130\sb80\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \f7\fs16 Displays the channel for the chat room. In the box, type the name of the channel where the chat room is located.
\par \pard\plain \s2\li115\ri130\sb120\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \b\f7\fs16 Connect to Server and List Channels
\par \pard\plain \li115\ri130\sb80\sl-240\slmult0\widctlpar \f7\fs16 Specifies that you want to connect to a server and have a list of channels to choose from when entering a chat room.
